summary: arya stark: has a deep connection to the old gods. they literally tell her she is a stark and a daughter of the north when she...
body:
arya stark: has a deep connection to the old gods. they literally tell her she is a stark and a daughter of the north when she prays to them for advice. which they do not do for any other character in this series. arya believes they returned needle to her and the weirwood in arya’s dreams also calls her true name even in braavos.

arya stark: has a close bond to her direwolf - the living sigil of house stark. nymeria has formed her own massive pack of wolves. like her bond human she is committed to her pack. arya is a powerful warg able to maintain the bond despite years of separation and an ocean between them. she also uses her skinchanging abilities on cats. the northern magic is strong in her blood.

arya stark: is the only stark child to get ned stark’s “the pack survives” speech its her main motivator is life. she values her family, friends and community above all else. arya feels it is her responsibility to protect and provide for her people. she prioritizes their needs above her own. she remembers ned’s lessons about the man who passe the setence should swing the sword too

arya stark: is the stark closest to winterfells smallfolk. she cherishes them and listens to what they say just like ned taught his heir. his words were to know your people and let them know you “dont ask them to die for a stranger” again, arya is the only living stark child to recall this lesson. the smallfolk affectionately called her arya underfoot. they knew her very well. to arya needle is winterfalls grey walls and the laughter of its people.

arya stark: also has a notable connection to the northern army and lords. she served roose bolton and was kept prisoner in harrenhal same as robett glover. arya helps feels free him and his men. arya gives mercy to dying northern at the stoney sept too in the form of one last drink of water but she is able to watch as they are ultimately killed for their crimes. 

arya stark: has lived the life of a servant and member of the lower class. she has done all the manual labor that the upper class take for granted like cooking, cleaning, serving, and mending clothes. she understands the burden of these duties because she has experienced them first hand. 

arya stark: has keen observational skills, can speak multiple languages, is good with mathematics, is stated to be more suited to running a household than her older sister, can detect when people are lying, has learned to carefully conceal her own thoughts and feelings 

arya stark: is very concerned with the pursuit of justice often for crimes that are ignored or even encouraged by the ruling class (torture, murder and rape - usually against the smallfolk) she even challenged the crown prince when he was harming mycah. arya acted as a ruler should on the banks of the trident by protecting an innocent. 

arya stark: is a pragmatic, compassionate, determined and brave girl. she acts decisively and boldly. she uses “the true seeing” to accurately assess situations and remembers exactly how things happened. she does not make a habit of hiding from the truth. 

arya stark: thinks winterfell is “arya’s place” and desperately wants to return. in grrm’s own words that is what shes always wanted. she is tired of running and craves a safe, stable community with her pack

the fandom: arya doesnt have anything to offer the north bc she doesnt like dresses so she will sail west of westeros in the end

Okay let’s talk about Arya and Gendry.

Remember when Arya was shocked about Gendry saying, that he wanted to stay at Btotherhood without banners? He said that they’re like a family and that he never had one. Arya replied: “I can be your family!” Gendry: “You won’t be my family. You’ll be my lady.”

I died at this thing! It was so heartbreaking pls let’s hope that they meet again!😭🙏🏻

summary: The Birds sing once more by AzraelGFG         |         Chapter 46: Arya
title: The Birds sing once more by AzraelGFG         |         Chapter 46: Arya
excerpt: An Archive of Our Own, a project of the Organization for Transformative Works
description:
The whole time in Braavos Arya always double checked if she was followed by someone, she suspicious. She doubted that the faceless men were still after her, but you could never know. After all, she thought she had seen Jaqen H’ghar more than once in the crowds of people she had seen in the city and once even nodding to her. Not threatening though, but…in respect?

But maybe her mind was playing games with her because she was here again.

summary: Do you think it's possible that will be no winterfell in the end? This fire from leak photos seems pretty bad
question: Do you think it's possible that will be no winterfell in the end? This fire from leak photos seems pretty bad
answer: I think it will be rebuilt. The Starks didn’t fix the damage done by Ramsay so we didn’t get the payoff to Bran’s poignant last moment in ACoK but we might get it by the end of the season. It would be great to see people working on restoring the ancient castle. It would send a message to the viewers that no matter what happens to them, the Starks will keep rebuilding.
